page.title: 02Liphook to Linchmere
page.content: cover the area, although only the latter is wholly contained within the block. The quite unspoilt hamlet of Linchmere is set betwixt linchmere and Stanley Commons and is composed of an ancient church built beside a narrow lane flanked by a collection of attractive mature cottages and a handful of large imposing residences. Half a mile to the north east of the church is a District Council estate of 40 houses and bungalows. Stanely and Linchmere Commons are covered by beach,birch and oak trees as is most of the surrounding area, although here, the traditional woodland is being replaced by the commercially profitable conifer type of tree.
